\ Cross-system seam torture, part 1 of 2: build a deliberately awkward live
\ state that crosses many subsystems at once, force a GC with it all live,
\ then save an image.  Part 2 (134) reloads it in a SEPARATE process, so
\ every piece must survive serialization, a fresh ASLR layout, and GC.

\ dispatch seam: a fused superword, an inlined call, recursion + a branch
variable g1   6 to g1
variable g2   7 to g2
: prod  vvf* g1 g2 ;
: inc   1 + ;
inline
: dbl   dup + ;
: poly  |> x |  x dbl inc ;
: sumto dup 0 > if dup 1 - sumto + then ;

\ logic seam: a bound logic var, and a pair sharing a bound var (reify must
\ preserve the sharing)
variable V   lvar to V   V 99 ~ drop
variable pr   lvar to X   [( X X null )] to pr   X 5 ~ drop

\ fact-database seam: an indexed relation with two rows
variable rel
[ :role ] relation to rel
rel { :name :gandalf :role :wizard } assert drop
rel { :name :frodo  :role :hobbit } assert drop

\ continuation seam: capture a slice mid-computation and stash it
: shifter shift ;
: ex  reset 99 shifter 2 * ;
variable k
ex  to k  drop

\ a matrix held in a variable
variable mat
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix to mat

\ make some garbage, then force a collection with all of the above live
[: [ 0 0 0 0 ] drop :] 2000 times
gc

clear
"/tmp/lf-torture.image" save-image
